dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset contains GIS data for Nepal Districts. Districts are not officially recognized as part of the new federal structure, nevertheless they are often used for coordinating the humanitarian response.

Consts.useLimit: See the COD/FOD Registry Terms of Use. This does not replace any terms of use information provided with the dataset.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. District names converted from ALL CAPS to Proper Case. 2. Created and populated District p-code field. Values come from the District p-code section of the Admin2 p-codes. 3. As instructed by IMO, ITOS has constructed p-codes using 2-letter ISO code "NL" in ITOS format. 4. Created and populated Admin0 name and p-code fields. 5. Districts "Rukum" and "Nawalparasi" did not nest with the Admin1 layer. As instructed by IMO, ITOS split districts "Rukum" and "Nawalparasi" in two. District name attribution has been changed to reflect this: "Rukum" with Admin1 "5" attribution has new district name "Rukum East". "Rukum" with Admin1 "6" attribution has new district name "Rukum West". "Nawalparasi" with Admin1 "5" attribution has new district name "Nawalparasi West". "Nawalparasi" with Admin1 "4" attribution has new district name "Nawalparasi East".
